ABUJA â€“ President Muhammadu Buhari has just intimated to Nigerians that he will be in London, United Kingdom, for an additional week. According to the presidency, Buhari is staying one week longer in order to meet an appointment with his Dentist, who has started attending to him. Femi Adesina, who disclosed the information in a terse statement on Tuesday, noted that the Specialist requires to see the President in another five days for a procedure already commenced. Buhari who is serving out his last term in office and is expected to bow out on May 29th, this month had joined other world leaders to attend the coronation of King Charles lll on May 6, 2023. He was expected back in the country on Sunday, May 7th until the statement emanated from his media aide indicating that he will spend a week more.